.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH mp-keygen 1  "mp-keygen 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
mp\-keygen \- Manage ed25519 key pairs for moshpit
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmp\-keygen\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR]... [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage ed25519 key pairs for moshpit
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Turn up logging verbosity (multiple will turn it up more)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Turn down logging verbosity (multiple will turn it down more)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
mp\-keygen\-generate(1)
Generate a new ed25519 public/private key pair
.TP
mp\-keygen\-verify(1)
Verify a public key fingerprint or randomart image
.TP
mp\-keygen\-fingerprint(1)
Display the fingerprint of the given public key
.TP
mp\-keygen\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
